[SN]TITLE[SN]
Ulster v Oyonnax : Craig Gilroy return is one of eight changes

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Craig Gilroy is fit to resume his place in the Ulster team for Sunday's rearranged European Champions Cup Pool One game against Oyonnax in France.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Gilroy's inclusion at full-back is one of eight changes from the side that lost to Munster in the Pro12 last week.
Ian Humphreys and Paul Marshall are selected as the half-back partnership.
Sam Arnold starts his first European game on the right wing while forwards Ricky Lutton, Lewis Stevenson and Roger Wilson are named in the starting XV.
Lutton replaces prop Wiehahn Herbst, who has failed to recover from a knock he sustained in the defeat at Kingspan Stadium last weekend, with Bronson Ross providing front-row cover among the replacements.
Stevenson comes in for the injured Alan O'Connor in the second row while Wilson replaces Nick Williams at number eight.
Regular first-choice half-back pairing Paddy Jackson and Ruan Pienaar occupy places on the replacements' bench, having been rested as part of the Ulster coaching staff's player management programme.
